<P>
   PRISON (Phoenix) {ndash} Twenty years ago, the number of women
behind bars in Arizona was barely enough to fill one prison wing.
</P>
<P>
   But their ranks have swollen so much that female felons now
warrant their own prison, proof that crime is an equal-opportunity
employer.
</P>
<P>
   Female inmates are still scattered among five prisons throughout
the state. But by October, they all will move to the Arizona State
Prison at Perryville in Goodyear. The move is necessary, according
to officials with the Arizona Department of Corrections, as a
cost-cutting measure in the face of a booming female prison
population. The number of female inmates has exploded since 1980,
when just 171 women w
</P>
