<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    A mouse you'll want around the office
 &HT;    By Shaun Conlin
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   The next iteration of Microsoft's IntelliMouse line is the
IntelliMouse Optical ($55; www.microsoft.com; for PC and Mac),
complete with the trackball-less, any-surface, never-gum, supremely
accurate ``IntelliEye'' laser reader in its belly. The most
ambitious descendent yet, the USB or PS/2 mouse boasts easy
Internet interfacing with the requisite left and right buttons on
top, a combination scroll wheel and third button nestled in
between, plus a thumb and pinky button on each side insinuated as
``forward'' and ``back'' commands on a browser _ or any function
the user cares to program. A symmetrical, ergonomic device, the
side buttons also accommodate left handed users.
</P>
<P>
   A great, high-tech mouse for all, lefties included, providing
they never share their computer with a righty nor ever use a
righty's computer, in which case, all involved are going to feel
backward.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
