<SLUG> BC-TECH-GAME-REVIEW0808-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    New Dreamcast titles have promise
 &HT;    By Troy Oxford
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Sega Dreamcast owners probably saved some money on
games the last few months. Besides the much sought after ``Virtua
Tennis,'' Capcom's ``Marvel vs. Capcom 2'' and the sleeper hit
``Wacky Races,'' the games of late June and July weren't that
spectacular. August, however, will be a different story.
</P>
<P>
   As the Oct. 26 launch of the PlayStation 2 draws closer, gamers
are going to see some very impressive Dreamcast titles as a prelude
to the game console competition.
</P>
<P>
   Some of the titles to look forward to this month:
</P>
<P>
   ``Seaman'' (coming Wednesday): A one-of-a-kind title from Sega,
``Seaman'' redefines the virtual pet. With the addition of a
microphone peripheral, you raise, nurture or abuse a wisecracking
fish/man.
</P>
<P>
   ``Deep Fighter'' (Wednesday): With various deep-sea vehicles and
interesting missions, this underwater title from Ubi Soft looks
promising.
</P>
<P>
   ``Ecco the Dolphin'' (Aug. 16): Another aquatic adventure game,
``Ecco the Dolphin'' looks amazing. The undersea world, marine life
and visual effects represent some of the best graphics on the
Dreamcast yet.
</P>
<P>
   ``WWF Royal Rumble'' (Aug. 17): All of your favorite WWF
superstars clobber away in this good-looking wrestling game. With
nine possible wrestlers in the ring at once, this looks like it
will be a smackdown good time.
</P>
<P>
   ``Test Drive V-Rally'' (Aug. 23): This off-road racing title
from Infogrames looks very cool. The game features a big selection
of cars, more than 80 tracks and game play in 12 countries.
</P>
<P>
   ``Ultimate Fighting Championship'' (Aug. 30): From the
developers of ``Tony Hawk Pro Skater'' for the Dreamcast comes this
intense fighting simulator. The game features a unique fighting
system, an array of moves and beautifully crafted 3-D models.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
