<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'')
</P>
<P>
   ARCHDIOCESE-TEENS (San Francisco) _ A decision by the
Archdiocese of San Francisco to no longer employ teenagers as
rectory workers not only takes away opportunities from kids but
fails to address the problem of abusive priests, said child
advocates and community activists. By JULIAN GUTHRIE.
</P>
<P>
   SEGAL-TRIAL (San Francisco) _ The day after Anton Segal got
smacked hard on the head by an angry man with a makeshift weapon,
friends around the world rushed to his side. They came from as far
as Hong Kong to stand by Segal, 28, while he lay in San Francisco
General Hospital, unable to recover from a blow that cracked open
his skull. On Nov. 24, 1998 _ three days after the attack _ Segal's
famously fine mind died with his body. Daniel Alas goes on trial
for the murder. By MICHAEL DOUGAN.
</P>
<P>
   FEATURES/LIFESTYLE (``l'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BIGFOOT (San Francisco) _ Researchers trying to legitimize the
search for Bigfoot have a mortal enemy, more fearsome than any
grizzly bear or armed wilderness hermit. The 1970s. Think back to
comic books. Monster trucks. Lee Majors in a polyester suit.
Reports of giant hairy bipeds walking across the Pacific Northwest
and parts of Canada go back nearly 200 years. By PETER HARTLAUB.
</P>
