</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    A monumental reopening
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Heading to our nation's capital soon? Be sure to stop
by the newly renovated Washington Monument. The 115-year-old
memorial reopened to the public last week. Workers spent three
years fixing cracks in the marble and improving the observation
deck at the top of the 555-foot structure. Free tours run from 9
a.m. to 5 p.m. every day. For more on the monument, go to
www.nps.gov/wamo/home.htm.
</P>
<P>
   MATH CLASS IS FUN
</P>
<P>
   Girls who think math just doesn't add up can turn to a Web site
designed for them to get some help. ColorMathPink.com is an
Internet site to help girls of all ages succeed in math. Find a
free tutor, get help with homework or examine your math anxiety. Of
course, boys can use the services, too!
</P>
