<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ Q: If it is not too expensive, I would like to
get my son a replica of the Maltese Falcon, like in the movie. I
have no idea where to start looking, so you came to mind.
</P>
<P>
   _ Pam Latham
</P>
<P>
   A: How about $50? The folks at Captain Bijou,
www.captainbijou.com or (256) 837-0049, sell these actual-size
plaster, jet-black-enamel-painted replicas of the famous Bogie
prop.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Is it really hotter than it used to be? My husband recently
attended his 45th high school reunion in San Antonio, and we all
commented on how much hotter it seems now than it was then. Is that
possible? Or were we just younger, unaware of air conditioning, or
what?
</P>
<P>
   _ J. Keith
</P>
<P>
   A: Yes, in the last 10 years, the Earth has warmed approximately
1.2 degrees, reports the National Weather Service. Stir in global
warming, increased urbanization and the human adaptation to air
conditioning and I agree, it is hotter than it used to be. Q:
Please tell me where I can purchase aluminum straws. I bought a few
of them years ago. They are very attractive, handy and dishwasher
safe.
</P>
<P>
   _ N. Roberts
</P>
<P>
   A: Restoration Hardware sells aluminum tea straws with a
spoon-shaped bottom ($2.50 each or six for $15). Prefer to stay in
the house? Order at www.restorationhardware.com or by phone at
(800) 762-1005.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am interested in writing to Queen Elizabeth II. Could you
