</P>
<P>
   SCIENCE-MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   CONNSUMERS-HMO _I want my HMO. That's the cry of hundreds of
Georgia seniors who have seen their Medicare HMO plans _ plans that
offered them annual physicals, vision tests and cheap prescriptions
_ evaporate within the past two years. It's a national crisis
brought on by low government reimbursement and rising health care
costs. And although there are 10 proposed laws to fix the
situation, it's leaving a lot of elderly with a traditional
Medicare plan _ with all those traditionally uncovered costs _ like
those very expensive drugs. With a tip box on what to do if your
plan suddenly folds. (Lore, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   HEALTH-WATER _ Health benefits of drinking water, why you need
to, how much you should drink. (Walker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: With box on foods that have a lot of water content and
photo.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BOTTLED-WATER _ Health experts and environmental officials say
there is no reason to believe bottled water is safer than tap. In
fact, fewer regs govern bottled water, and a new state survey of
tap-water supplies gives it a clean bill of health. Plus: details
on choosing a water filter, for those who have lingering concerns
or want to improve taste. (Seabrook, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
20.
</P>
<P>
   MEDICINE-FLAVORS _ Sour apple, cinnamon, root beer or mint
chocolate _ choose a flavor. Parents can take a vacation from
tantrums and screeching cries since pharmacist-technician Kenneth
Kramm invented Flavorx _ 42 flavors to cover the bitter taste of
some prescribed and over-the-counter liquid medicine. ``The most
popular flavors are bubblegum, cherry and grape,'' said Edee
Gosnell, a registered pharmacist and owner of Medicap Pharmacy in
Eaton, Ohio. (Dayton Daily News). WITH PHOTO.
</P>
