r l BC-WESTNILE-PREVENTION-T     08-07 0356
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WESTNILE-PREVENTION-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE BUZZ ON PREVENTION
</HEADLINE>
 
 (EDS: Accompanies TEXAS-WEST NILE VIRUS)  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Mosquitoes bite the hand that breeds them, say public health
officials.
</P>
<P>
   ``At least one-quarter of our service requests are from people
who have standing water with mosquitoes breeding in their own
yards,'' said Scott Sawlis of the Dallas County Health Department.
``We find birdbaths and flowerpots or the dishes under flowerpots
and piles of old tires filled with water. Even treated city water,
once it has been sitting in the sun a day or so, will breed
mosquitoes. Used tires are basically mosquito condos.''
</P>
<P>
   To prevent mosquito infestation, the city of Fort Worth Public
Health Department suggests:
</P>
<P>
   _Empty or get rid of cans, buckets, bottles, old tires, empty
pots, plant saucers and other containers that hold water.
</P>
<P>
   _Clean clogged rain gutters on a regular basis.
</P>
<P>
   _Turn over plastic wading pools when not in use and do not allow
water to stagnate in birdbaths.
</P>
<P>
   _Use landscaping to eliminate low areas where puddles may
develop on your property, and water yards carefully so that no
water stands for several days.
</P>
<P>
   _For personal protection, public health officials recommend a
repellent containing the chemical DEET.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's best to stay inside with windows up and air conditioner
going,'' Sawlis said. ``When you are outside, cover up with light
colors and avoid the late evening when shadows help attract
mosquitoes. If you are outside, especially in the evening, spray or
rub on some repellent that contains DEET. It's been around since
the '40s and is still the best product out there.''
</P>
<P>
   For children, he recommended spraying the outside of clothing
and wiping repellent on ears and necks after you spray it on your
own hands.
</P>
<P>
   ``Also with kids, you may want to use a product with less than
10 percent DEET. I want maximum protection, so I use 24 to 26
percent on myself, but we recommend less for children.''
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
