   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BOTTLED-WATER _ Health experts and environmental officials say
there is no reason to believe bottled water is safer than tap. In
fact, fewer regs govern bottled water, and a new state survey of
tap-water supplies gives it a clean bill of health. Plus: details
on choosing a water filter, for those who have lingering concerns
or want to improve taste. (Seabrook, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
20.
</P>
<P>
   MEDICINE-FLAVORS _ Sour apple, cinnamon, root beer or mint
chocolate _ choose a flavor. Parents can take a vacation from
tantrums and screeching cries since pharmacist-technician Kenneth
Kramm invented Flavorx _ 42 flavors to cover the bitter taste of
some prescribed and over-the-counter liquid medicine. ``The most
popular flavors are bubblegum, cherry and grape,'' said Edee
Gosnell, a registered pharmacist and owner of Medicap Pharmacy in
Eaton, Ohio. (Dayton Daily News). WITH PHOTO.
