<P>
   WHICH COLLEGE? EARLY DECISION OPTIONS AND THE CAMPUS TOUR
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGE-OPTIONS-LIFEBEAT _ From a high school senior's
perspective, the advantages of applying to college ahead of the
pack are tempting: not only do you receive a speedy ``yea'' or
``nay,'' but your odds of being accepted increase markedly.
However, this tactic can limit a student's scholarship
opportunities. Also, some students simply need more time to look
around. If possible, students should schedule campus tours and
interviews at the colleges that interest them. By Kristen Carr.
</P>
<P>
   MIDDLE EASTERN FILMMAKERS FASCINATE THE WEST
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-FILM-LIFEBEAT _ Today, with intermittent peace talks and
slightly relaxed borders, the Middle East seems hesitantly
welcoming yet still esoteric enough to provoke fascination in the
West. Filmmakers and video artists from Iran and elsewhere in the
Middle East have found that repression and even war inspire
passionate, provocative works of art. By Brad Gooch.
</P>
<P>
   VERSATILE HYDRANGEAS ENHANCE ANY GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   GARDENS-HYDRANGEAS-LIFEBEAT _ Hydrangeas are among those species
for which the word ``remarkable'' can be used without exaggeration.
How many plant families can trace their history back 70 million
years, are native to three continents, contain members that are
bushes, trees and vines, are both deciduous and evergreen and have
flowers that can completely change color from year to year or
season to season? There's a hydrangea for any garden, from clay
pots to meticulously cultivated acres. By Michael Weishan.
</P>
<P>
   WHEN THE CURE FOR A MOTHER POSES A THREAT TO THE CHILD
</P>
<P>
   PREGNANCY-CANCER-LIFEBEAT _ At long last pregnant with her first
child, the author learned three weeks later that she had an
aggressive form of breast cancer. She and her husband wrestled with
the decision of whether to abort the pregnancy and decided to go
ahead. Their healthy child is now five years old, but the cancer
has returned several times since. However the author says, ``I know
that I would not have done anything differently.'' By Jana
Striegel-Wilson.
</P>
