<P>
   GORE-LIEBERMAN (Nashville, Tenn.) _ Vice President Al Gore
picked Sen. Joseph Lieberman of Connecticut to be his running mate,
putting a Jewish candidate on a national ticket for the first time
in history. Gore will not formally announce his selection until
Tuesday. Lieberman, 58, is known chiefly on the national stage as
the first Democrat to condemn President Clinton during the Monica
Lewinsky scandal, branding his behavior ``immoral.'' By Katharine
Q. Seelye.
</P>
<P>
   With photos, NYT2,3,8,10,11.
</P>
<P>
   LIEBERMAN-PROFILE (Undated) _ A man-in-the-news profile of
Senator Lieberman. By Robert D. McFadden.
