add rocket fuel to the new economy. On Monday, Merrill Lynch's star
Internet analyst re-entered the atmosphere, downgrading 10 of the
26 companies he covers. Four months after the start of the April
bloodbath that halted the Internet's unfettered charge, one of the
most reliable of Internet bulls is finally showing signs of doubt.
By Danny Hakim.
