(NYT27) SIACHEN GLACIER, in the western Himalayas -- August 7, 2000
-- INDIA-PAKISTAN -- A Pakistani soldier stands vigil in the high
peaks of the western Himalayas in May, 1999. Pakistan, like India,
has some 3,000 soldiers fighting in a border war in the region that
is now 15 years old. American intelligence agencies warned
President Clinton this spring that the likelihood of a war between
India and Pakistan that could escalate into a nuclear conflict has
increased significantly, according to officials with access to the
secret intelligence. (Barry Bearak/New York Times Photo)
(NYT26) NEW YORK -- Aug. 7, 2000 -- NY-POLICE-SAFIR -- Police
Commissioner Howard Safir, who has presided over a department beset
by racial incidents at the same time that crime has dropped
dramatically, will be leaving the New York Police Department next
month, police sources with direct knowledge of Safir's plans
confirmed Monday. Safir with Mayor Rudolph Giuliani, right, during
a news conference at police headquarters in 1997. (Librado
Romero/The New York Times)
(NYT25) NEW YORK -- Aug. 7, 2000 -- NY-TOURISM -- The number of
tourists visiting the city reached an all-time high in 1999, with
36.7 million visitors spending an estimated $15.5 billion, Mayor
Rudolph Giuliani said Monday. Giuliani and Cristyne
Lategano-Nicholas, NYC &AMP; Company president talk to reporters about
tourism in the city, Monday. release New York City's
record-breaking official tourism statistics for 1999, showing the
total number of visitors increasing 11 percent over 1998 to 36.7
million and growing in almost every major category. ( Ruby
Washington/The New York Times)
