and Barnum &AMP; Bailey Circus to raise a custom-made Italian tent in
Bryant Park and present a high-end, one-ring, family-oriented
circus during the Thanksgiving and Christmas holidays. The Ringling
show hopes to turn a profit, and the nonprofit Big Apple Circus,
who for 20 years has pitched their French tent at Lincoln Center,
is crying foul. Regina Dobrovitskaya swings between elephants, with
William Woodcock, in `Bello and Friends,` during a Big Apple Circus
performance in 1999. (Sara Krulwich/The New York Times)
