President Al Gore picked Sen. Joseph Lieberman of Connecticut to be
his running mate, Monday. Lieberman, 58, is known chiefly on the
national stage as the first Democrat to condemn President Clinton
during the Monica Lewinsky scandal. Gore, who did not criticize
Clinton throughout the impeachment process, has had a difficult
time distancing himself from Clinton's personal behavior. Gore
looks on as Clinton denies a relationship with Lewinsky in 1998.
(Paul Hosefros/The New York Times)
