Democratic centrist much like Gore, although he is perceived to be
more conservative on matters like welfare reform. Lieberman looks
on as Gore addressed supporters in the Roosevelt Room of the White
House on enviromnetal issues in 1997. (Carol T. Powers/The New York
Times)
(NYT2) WASHINGTON -- Aug. 7, 2000 -- GORE-LIEBERMAN-1 -- Sen. Joe
Lieberman, D-Conn., is Vice President Al Gore's pick as his running
mate, Democratic officials said Monday. Lieberman, 58, is a
Democratic centrist much like Gore, although he is perceived to be
more conservative on matters like welfare reform. He also has a
reputation for moral rectitude. Like Gore, he was one of the few
Democrats to vote in favor of the Persian Gulf War. Lieberman in a
1999 file photo. (Justin Lane/The New York Times)
(NYT1) NEW YORK, Aug. 7, 2000 -- SUMMER-BAPTISM -- In a joyous rite
of summer, the United House of rayer for All People baptized
hundreds of people with a fire hose Sunday on a street in Harlem.
`I ask the Lord to bless the water of the New York reservoir,`
Bishop S. C. Madison prayed as the ceremony began Sunday afternoon.
(Michelle V. Agins/The New York Times)
