<HEADLINE>
BIOGRAPHICAL BOX ON LEIBERMAN
</HEADLINE>
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Joseph Isador Lieberman
</P>
<P>
   BORN: Feb. 24, 1942, Stamford, Conn.
</P>
<P>
   HOMETOWN: New Haven, Conn.
</P>
<P>
   EDUCATION: Stamford (Conn.) High School; B.A., L.L.B., Yale.
</P>
<P>
   CAREER HIGHLIGHTS: 1971-81, Connecticut state senator; 1975-81,
state Senate majority leader; 1983-89, Connecticut attorney
general; 1989-present, U.S. senator from Connecticut; committee
member, Armed Services, Environment and Public Works, Small
Business, Governmental Affairs; 1999-present, ranking Democrat,
Governmental Affairs Committee; 1995-present, chairman, Democratic
Leadership Council. Author of five books, most recently ``In Praise
of Public Life.''
</P>
<P>
   FAMILY: Married to the former Hadassah Freilich; they have one
daughter together, Hana, 12; from previous marriages, he has a son,
Matt, 32, and a daughter, Rebecca, 31, and she has a son, Ethan,
24.
</P>
<P>
   OTHER INTERESTS: Studying the Torah, reading, following the New
York Yankees.
</P>
