<HEADLINE>
GASPING ON THE FIRST DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVINE, Calif. _ USC opened what coach Paul Hackett billed as
his toughest training camp Monday, and true freshman defensive end
Nathan Goodson appeared to be the first casualty.
</P>
<P>
   Goodson, one of USC's top recruits, has had one of the most
unpleasant reactions to training camp, vomiting twice after being
run to the point of exhaustion by defensive line coach Ed Orgeron.
</P>
<P>
   ``I came ill-prepared and reality has kicked me in the butt,''
Goodson said good-naturedly. ``I came into camp out of shape. I was
gagging for air. Everything I got I expected.''
</P>
<P>
   Goodson weighed 265 pounds in high school but ballooned to 285
in the summer and currently weighs 272.
</P>
<P>
   ``They come in and want to play, but they have to be prepared,''
Orgeron said. ``Their idea and my idea of conditioning are probably
two different things. It's a different game up here. He responded.
He wants to be good.''
</P>
<P>
   Otherwise, Hackett was pleased with the Trojans' conditioning,
saying none of the other players seemed to be straining during wind
sprints.
</P>
<P>
   __ Palmer pleases: Quarterback Carson Palmer appeared extremely
sharp for the first day, showing few of the timing problems with
receivers that Hackett anticipated. The sophomore continues to work
his way back from last year's broken collarbone.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think he looked great,'' Hackett said. ``This will be his
best day for a while. He's going to get tired now from all the
throwing. But he'll get it back by the middle of next week.''
</P>
<P>
   Palmer said the offense worked better than he expected for the
first day of practice.
</P>
<P>
   ``The offense is coming together pretty quickly,'' he said. ``I
was kind of surprised.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Late arrivals: Offensive lineman Zach Wilson and linebacker
Anthony Daye missed practice to finish summer school and are
expected today. Hackett said he hoped to know by Thursday if
defensive lineman Sagan Atuatasi would be eligible to join the
team. Atuatasi has been attending junior college.
</P>
<P>
   __ Injury report: Freshman defensive lineman Jamaal Williams
injured his leg in Monday's morning practice and was scheduled for
X-rays Monday night. Wide receiver Steve Stevenson suffered a
pulled hamstring and missed the afternoon practice.
</P>
<P>
   Defensive tackle Ryan Nielsen practiced just once to rest his
shoulder that underwent offseason surgery. Freshman tailback Chris
Howard remains limited from arthroscopic knee surgery and also
practiced once.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-07-00 2340EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
